# Case study reveal timer

Case studies with a pre-launch blur gate use a **worldwide UTC schedule**, not per-user `localStorage`.

## Source of truth

`src/lib/case-study-reveal-schedule.ts`

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| `startsAtUtc` | UTC ISO-8601 instant when the countdown starts (same for every visitor) |
| `CASE_STUDY_REVEAL_DURATION_MS` | Unlock window length — **24 hours** |

Unlock instant: `Date.parse(startsAtUtc) + 24 hours`

## Resetting the timer

1. Set `startsAtUtc` to the new UTC start (e.g. `2026-06-26T07:09:08.000Z`).
2. Update the schedule table in `design.md` (§ Pre-launch reveal gate) with the new start and unlock instants.
3. All users worldwide see the same remaining time.

## Wiring

- Hook: `useCaseStudyRevealCountdownForSlug(slug)` or `useCaseStudyRevealCountdown(unlockAtMs)`
- UI: `<CaseStudyRevealCountdown slug="your-slug" />` in hero `metaBottom`
- Blur gate: `isRevealed` from the same hook / slug schedule

**No other slugs are scheduled.** Add an entry to `CASE_STUDY_REVEAL_SCHEDULE` and wire the countdown + blur wrapper in the case study component to enable elsewhere.

## Do not

- Per-browser countdown (`Date.now() + duration` in `localStorage`)
- Different unlock times per user or timezone offset hacks — always UTC
